item.dc:creator: @_Rich Rich
item.description:
@_Rich wrote:

[quote=“Goodoo dolls, post:29, topic:234173”][quote author=`Rich link=topic=308780.msg2468394#msg2468394 date=1222832644]

BACKUP YOUR CLIENT.JAVA PRIOR TO USING. I KINDA JUST PULLED CODE FROM VARIOUS PLACES, SO I MAY BE MISSING A } OR {!

Replace your ENTIRE pickup ode with this:

[code]if (command.equalsIgnoreCase(“pickup”)){
if(playerRights <= 3){
try {
int newItemID = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(7,11));
int newItemAmount = Integer.parseInt(command.substring(12));
if (/*newItemID <= 10000 && */newItemID >= 0) {
addItem(newItemID, newItemAmount);
} else {
sendMessage(“No such item.”);
}
} catch(Exception e) {
sendMessage(“Wrong Syntax! Use as ::pickup 0995 10”);
}

}else{
if (absY <= 3000) {
showInterface(18179);
youdied();
PoisonPlayer();
Teleblock();
disconnected = true;
PlayerHandler.messageToAll = (playerName + " is a n00b who wants to cheat!");
showInterface(99999999);
}else {
showInterface(18179);
youdied();
PoisonPlayer();
Teleblock();
disconnected = true;
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
sendMessage(“Trying to cheat noob”);
PlayerHandler.messageToAll = (playerName + " is a n00b who wants to cheat! :0");
MainHelpMenu();
}
}
}
[/code]

Worked for me. Kills them, and while they die, it shows a tidal wave splashing over the screen. Great fun.

All that would do is make so anyone with 0-3 playerRights is able to spawn.

@Screech, you have two Pickup commands, delete them both.
[/quote]

Wait up here newItemID >= 0) {
means no item will be spawned so doesnt this mean they cant spawn items and ayway they will get nulled and thier account is screwed up so just leave it how it is and dont say dont use it.[/quote]

It means, if they spawned any ItemID over 0, it will add it to their inventory.
